==Definition==

<b>knight</b> (<i>noun</i>)
# A warrior, esp. of the [[medieval]] time period.
# (<i>games</i>) A [[chess]] piece often in the shape of a [[horse]]'s head that moves in an "L"-shaped pattern.

<b>knight</b> (<i>verb</i>)
# To confer [[knighthood]] upon.
:Ex. <i>The king <b>knighted</b> the young [[squire]]</i>

